oesn't%20work%2C%20Apple%20might%20have%20to%20rely%20on%20other%20tech%20giants%20(and%20rivals)%20for%20help%20or%20go%20on%20an%20expensive%20acquisition%20spree.%20I%20asked%20Apple%20about%20all%20this%20last%20week%20and%20have%20not%20heard%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226392e92e-d864-4b99-8dda-abbc5cc1a76b%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20building%20blocks%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20needs%20a%20multitude%20of%20AI%20building%20blocks.%20To%20give%20you%20a%20better%20idea%2C%20take%20a%20look%20at%20what%20Google%20has%20put%20in%20place%20over%20the%20decades%20to%20ensure%20it's%20ready%20for%20this%20AI%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20the%20example%20of%20Flow%2C%20a%20new%20generative%20AI%20tool%20Google%20unveiled%20last%20week%20that%20helps%20creators%20churn%20out%20professional%20videos.%20Many%20huge%20AI%20building%20blocks%20lie%20underneath%20this%20product.%20Here's%20a%20rough%20look%20at%20some%20of%20them%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22896%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20chart%20showing%20the%20technology%20supporting%20Google's%20Flow%20video-creation%20service%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68362e566ffb6822ec619384%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221344%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20chart%20showing%20the%20technology%20supporting%20Google's%20Flow%20video-creation%20service.%3Cp%3EBI%20reporting%2FChatGPT%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-video-veo-openai-sora-comaprison-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EVeo%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20Google's%20video-generation%20AI%20model%2C%20now%20in%20its%20third%20iteration.%20That%20wouldn't%20exist%20without%20all%20those%20YouTube%20videos%20to%20train%20on.%20Who%20owns%20YouTube%3F%20Oh%20yeah%2C%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImagen%20is%20Google's%20image-generation%20model%2C%20now%20in%20its%20fourth%20incarnation.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-gemini-bard%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGemini%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20Google's%20answer%20to%20ChatGPT.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-researchers-have-turned-agi-race-upside-down-with-paper-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETransformer%20architecture%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20research%20breakthrough%20that%20made%20generative%20AI%20possible.%20That%20was%20invented%20at%20Google%20around%202017.%20Tensor%20Processing%20Units%20(TPUs)%20are%20a%20type%20of%20Google%20AI%20chip%20(more%20on%20that%20below).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20way%20more%20than%20this%2C%20though.%20Google%20has%20indexed%20everything%20on%20the%20web%20and%20has%20done%20so%20for%20decades.%20It%20slurps%20up%20mountains%20of%20other%20information%20in%20multiple%20ways.%20This%20can%20be%20used%20as%20training%20data%20to%20develop%20powerful%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229b1bfbdd-76c9-469c-acf7-9c231302814c%5C%22%3ELarry%20Page's%20AI%20vision%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20cofounder%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D1OT_Uj2z3Z0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELarry%20Page%3C%2Fa%3E%20talked%20about%20this%20in%20an%20interview%20back%20in%202000%20when%20most%20of%20us%20were%20worrying%20about%20whether%20our%20dishwashers%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fglobal-it-outage-y2k-24-years-later-crowdstrike-cyber-expert-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EY2K%3C%2Fa%3E%20compliant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BArtificial%20intelligence%20would%20be%20the%20ultimate%20version%20of%20Google%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20when%20Google%20was%20barely%20two%20years%20old.%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20understand%2C%20you%20know%2C%20exactly%20what%20you%20wanted.%20And%20it%20would%20give%20you%20the%20right%20thing.%20And%20that's%20obviously%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20you%20know%2C%20it%20would%20be%20able%20to%20answer%20any%20question%2C%20basically%2C%20because%20almost%20everything%20is%20on%20the%20web%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20Google%20had%20about%206%2C000%20computers%20to%20store%20roughly%20100%20copies%20of%20the%20web.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20computation%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20data%20that%20didn't%20used%20to%20be%20available%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20cherubic%20Page%20explained.%20%26quot%3BFrom%20an%20engineering%20scientific%20standpoint%2C%20building%20things%20to%20make%20use%20of%20this%20is%20a%20really%20interesting%20intellectual%20exercise.%20So%20I%20expected%20to%20be%20doing%20that%20for%20a%20while.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Google%20went%20public%20as%20a%20search%20engine%20provider%20in%202004%2C%20it%20was%20already%20an%20AI%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226f890d45-6a1a-44dd-9eec-38a1ff951656%5C%22%3EFrom%20AlexNet%20to%20TensorFlow%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202012%2C%20researchers%20developed%20a%20major%20AI%20breakthrough%20when%20they%20trained%20computers%20to%20recognize%20and%20classify%20objects%20just%20by%20%26quot%3Blooking%26quot%3B%20at%20them.%20Alex%20Krizhevsky%2C%20Ilya%20Sutskever%2C%20and%20their%20advisor%20Geoffrey%20Hinton%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto%20developed%20this%20AlexNet%20technology%20and%20formed%20a%20company%20called%20DNNresearch.%20Google%20bought%20it%20in%202013%2C%20gaining%20all%20the%20intellectual%20property%2C%20including%20its%20source%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20there's%20one%20building%20block%20I%20would%20highlight%20that%20led%20to%20Google's%20Flow%20product%2C%20it's%20this%20moment%2C%20which%20occurred%20at%20least%20%3Cem%3E12%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20Google%20bought%20DeepMind%2C%20a%20secretive%20AI%20lab%20run%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-demis-hassabis-deepmind-founder-ai-google-nobel-prize-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDemis%20Hassabis%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmustafa-suleyman-microsoft-ai-chief-main-goals-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMustafa%20Suleyman%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20building%20block%20inspired%20Elon%20Musk%20to%20bring%20OpenAI%20into%20being%2C%20as%20a%20counterweight%20to%20Google's%20growing%20AI%20power.%20That%20was%20%3Cem%3Eover%20a%20decade%20ago.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Hassabis%20and%20DeepMind%20now%20lead%20many%20of%20Google's%20most%20impressive%20AI%20creations.%20Suleyman%20runs%20big%20AI%20stuff%20at%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Google's%20big%20I%2FO%20conference%20in%202016%2C%20the%20company%20brought%20in%20me%20and%20a%20bunch%20of%20other%20journalists%20to%20learn%20about%20%26quot%3Bmachine%20learning%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20branch%20of%20AI.%20Hinton%20and%20other%20AI%20pioneers%20spent%20hours%20scribbling%20on%20a%20whiteboard%20trying%20to%20explain%20how%20this%20complex%20tech%20worked%20%E2%80%94%20to%20an%20audience%20that%20probably%20got%20Bs%20or%20lower%20in%20high%20school%20math.%20It%20was%20painful%2C%20but%20again%20it%20shows%20how%20far%20ahead%20Google%20has%20been%20in%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20same%20year%2C%20Google%20unveiled%20TPUs%2C%20a%20series%20of%20home-grown%20AI%20chips%20that%20compete%20with%20Nvidia's%20GPUs.%20Google%20uses%20TPUs%20in%20its%20own%20data%20centers%20and%20also%20rents%20them%20out%20to%20other%20companies%20and%20developers%20via%20its%20cloud%20service.%20It%20even%20developed%20an%20AI%20framework%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftensorflow-google-ai-project-uber-nasa-twitter-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETensorFlow%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20support%20machine%20learning%20developers%2C%20although%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-pytorch-beat-google-tensorflow-jax-meta-ai-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta's%20open-source%20PyTorch%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20gained%20ground%20there%20lately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2278b88965-21e7-4c07-bb0d-edfc3a76f90f%5C%22%3EAn%20'AI-first'%20world%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20I%20attended%20I%2FO%20again.%20Google%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%20said%20the%20company%20is%20uniquely%20ready%20for%20the%20generative%20AI%20moment.%20It%20seems%20like%20a%20throw-away%20comment%2C%20though%20it%20represents%20a%20quarter%20of%20a%20century%20of%20work%20that%20began%20with%20Page's%20AI%20vision.%20Almost%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20Pichai%20said%20Google%20was%20moving%20toward%20an%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsundar-pichai-ai-first-world-2016-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI-first%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20computing%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224304%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Google%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%20delivers%20his%20keynote%20address%20during%20the%20Google%20I%2FO%202016%20developers%20conference%20in%20Mountain%20View%2C%20California%20May%2018%2C%202016.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682fbc03c6ad288d1481ba15%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222870%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoogle%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%20delivered%20the%20keynote%20at%20Google%20I%2FO%20in%202016.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FStephen%20Lam%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20building%20blocks%20are%20massively%20expensive%20to%20create%20and%20maintain.%20For%20instance%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falphabet-to-spend-big-ai-capex-q4-earnings-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20%2475%20billion%20of%20capex%20this%20year%2C%20mainly%20for%20AI%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20does%20Google%20power%20all%20these%20facilities%3F%20Well%2C%20it's%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20corporate%20purchasers%20of%20renewable%20energy%20and%20recently%20cut%20deals%20to%20develop%20three%20nuclear%20power%20stations.%20Without%20all%20this%2C%20Google%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20compete%20in%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222c9216b6-352d-48be-8dcc-7eda55d614e7%5C%22%3EApple's%20tricky%20situation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20lacks%20many%20of%20these%20building%20blocks.%20For%20instance%2C%20it%20doesn't%20run%20many%20large%20data%20centers%20and%20sometimes%20even%20uses%20Google%20facilities%20for%20important%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20when%20Apple%20device%20users%20do%20iCloud%20backups%2C%20they're%20often%20stored%20in%20Google%20data%20centers.%20When%20it%20came%20to%20training%20Apple%20AI%20models%20that%20power%20the%20iPhone%20maker's%20new%20Apple%20Intelligence%2C%20the%20company%20asked%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-ai-google-data-centers-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eadditional%20access%20to%20Google's%20TPUs%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20training%20runs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20rely%20on%20a%20rival%20like%20this%3F%20Well%2C%20Apple%20only%20started%20working%20on%20a%20home-grown%20AI%20chip%20for%20data%20centers%20in%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years.%20That's%20roughly%20seven%20years%20after%20Google%20TPUs%20came%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20data%20but%20has%20been%20cautious%20about%20using%20it%20for%20AI%20development%20due%20to%20user%20privacy%20concerns.%20It's%20tried%20to%20handle%20AI%20processing%20on%20devices%20such%20as%20iPhones%2C%20but%20these%20projects%20require%20massive%20computing%20power%20that%20only%20data%20centers%20can%20provide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20has%20also%20been%20slow%20to%20recruit%20AI%20talent.%20It%20didn't%20let%20AI%20researchers%20publish%20research%20papers%20publicly%2C%20or%20put%20limits%20on%20this.%20That%20has%20been%20a%20basic%20ingredient%20for%20recruiting%20this%20crucial%20talent%20over%20many%20years.%20Apple%20did%20hire%20AI%20pioneer%20John%20Giannandrea%20from%20Google%20in%202018%2C%20though%20he%20has%20struggled%20to%20make%20an%20impact%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported.%3C%2