%20a%20water-enhancing%20cartridge%20system%2C%20no-one%20else%20knew%20how%20to%20make%20it%20%E2%80%94%20so%20they%20figured%20it%20out%20themselves.%3Cp%3ECirkul%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECirkul's%20co-founders%20came%20up%20with%20a%20water-enhancing%20cartridge%20system%2C%20but%20couldn't%20find%20a%20manufacturer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhat%20started%20as%20a%20hand-made%20operation%20in%202018%20has%20now%20expanded%20to%20production%20in%20two%20states.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECEO%20Garrett%20Waggoner%20told%20BI%20that%20making%20in%20the%20US%20has%20been%20key%20to%20the%20company's%20quick%20growth.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20really%20important%20%E2%80%94%20and%20often%20overlooked%20%E2%80%94%20thing%20about%20coming%20up%20with%20a%20new%20product%20idea%20is%20finding%20a%20way%20to%20make%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20what%20Cirkul%20co-founders%20Garrett%20Waggoner%20and%20Andy%20Gay%20discovered%20when%20they%20came%20up%20with%20a%20concept%20for%20a%20water-enhancing%20flavor%20cartridge%20system%20back%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Cirkul%20cartridge%20was%20such%20a%20novel%20form%20factor%2C%20and%20no%20one%20had%20ever%20done%20anything%20like%20it%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20Waggoner%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20the%20product%20overseas%20wasn't%20even%20an%20option%2C%20since%20there%20weren't%20any%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fafina-shower-head-founder-tests-paying-more-american-made-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econtract%20manufacturers%20who%20could%20do%20the%20job%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20had%20to%20start%20doing%20it%20ourselves%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaggoner%20and%20Gay%20had%20%26quot%3Bno%20formal%20background%20in%20manufacturing%20or%20operations%2C%20but%20back%20in%202018%20we%20leased%20a%20little%20warehouse%20and%20started%20filling%20cartridges%20by%20hand%20at%20night.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBit%20by%20bit%2C%20the%20Tampa-based%20brand%20gained%20a%20following%20on%20social%20media%2C%20linked%20up%20with%20Walmart%2C%20announced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcirkul-flavored-water-bottle-startup-popularity-valuation-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20%241%20billon%20valuation%20in%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Waggoner%20said%20the%20company%20now%20has%20a%20million%20square%20feet%20of%20production%20space%20divided%20between%20Florida%20and%20Utah.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaggoner%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwest-paw-ceo-manufacturing-us-hard-american-made-dog-toys-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emaking%20his%20products%20in%20America%3C%2Fa%3E%20paired%20well%20with%20the%20company's%20original%20direct-to-consumer%20model%2C%20which%20allowed%20the%20team%20to%20quickly%20turn%20customer%20feedback%20into%20useful%20changes%2C%20rather%20than%20having%20to%20wait%20for%20a%20ship%20to%20cross%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20early%20days%2C%20if%20you%20dropped%20the%20bottle%20from%2C%20say%2C%20hip%20height%2C%20the%20cartridge%20would%20kind%20of%20break%20apart%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20very%20quickly%2C%20our%20engineering%20team%20identified%20manufacturing%20tolerance%20adjustments%20that%20strengthened%20that%20connection.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20rapid%20feedback%20loop%20was%20%26quot%3Bvital%20to%20helping%20the%20product%20grow%20up%20to%20where%20it%20is%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20expanding%20menu%20of%20flavors%20is%20still%20driven%20by%20customer%20feedback%2C%20with%20cartridges%20mixed%20and%20made%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20cartridges%2C%20Cirkul%20also%20sells%20a%20selection%20of%20plastic%20bottles%20(which%20the%20company%20makes%20here)%2C%20and%20a%20newer%20line%20of%20Stanley-style%20stainless%20steel%20tumblers%20(which%20are%20currently%20imported%2C%20though%20Waggoner%20said%20he's%20exploring%20ways%20to%20bring%20that%20production%20on-shore).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20decision%20to%20make%20his%20products%20primarily%20in%20the%20US%20was%20at%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-made-in-usa-american-brands-domestic-manufacturing-benefits-challenges-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emore%20about%20necessity%20than%20principle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Waggoner%20said%20he%20hasn't%20really%20seen%20outsourcing%20or%20off-shoring%20as%20attractive%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20growing%20so%20quickly%20that%2C%20to%20be%20honest%2C%20it's%20just%20never%20been%20a%20consideration%2C%20because%20we've%20been%20building%20our%20operations%20out%20continuously%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BFrankly%2C%20the%20team%20takes%20a%20lot%20of%20pride%20in%20it%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20lot%20of%20fun%20to%20see%20the%20team%20deliver%20something%20that%20is%20novel.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcirkul-ceo-making-product-in-us-helped-speed-up-growth-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748422561000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683609756ffb6822ec618b3a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcirkul-ceo-making-product-in-us-helped-speed-up-growth-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20Cirkul's%20co-founders%20came%20up%20with%20a%20water-enhancing%20cartridge%20system%2C%20no%20one%20else%20knew%20how%20to%20make%20it%20%E2%80%94%20so%20they%20figured%20it%20out%20themselves.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dreuter%40businessinsider.com%20(Dominick%20Reuter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A82%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcirkul-ceo-making-product-in-us-helped-speed-up-growth-2025-5%22%2C