%5C%22%5C%22%3Esex%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Combined%20with%20tightening%20client%20budgets%2C%20rates%20began%20to%20drop.%20I%20spoke%20with%20several%20sex%20workers%2C%20whose%20names%20have%20been%20changed%20in%20order%20to%20protect%20their%20identities%2C%20who%20turned%20to%20sex%20work%20to%20weather%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-slowdown-companies-take-longer-fill-open-roles-ghost-jobs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etough%20job%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%20to%20find%20that%20an%20overcrowded%20market%20is%20making%20the%20field%20far%20less%20lucrative%20for%20some.%20On%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FSexWorkers%2Fcomments%2F1jn0umv%2Fhas_lowering_your_rate_decreased_bookings%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sex%20workers%20have%20started%20discussing%20lowering%20their%20rates%20to%20attract%20more%20clients.%20One%20sex%20worker%20I%20spoke%20with%20reported%20a%2030%25%20drop%20in%20earnings%20since%202019.%20And%20now%2C%20as%20the%20economy%20lurches%20further%20into%20chaos%2C%20those%20who%20saw%20sex%20work%20as%20a%20possible%20backup%20plan%20are%20facing%20a%20tough%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20past%20four%20months%20this%20year%2C%20something%20has%20happened.%20People%20are%20way%20stingier%20than%20they%20were%2C%26quot%3B%20Hannah%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20lot%20quieter%20in%20the%20club%20this%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20graduates%20in%20the%20wake%20of%202020%2C%20sex%20work%20offered%20a%20rare%20form%20of%20economic%20opportunity%20during%20a%20time%20of%20historic%20job%20loss%2C%20stagnant%20wages%2C%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-cracking-job-market-layoffs-unemployment-recession-tariffs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecollapsing%20job%20market%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BSelling%20sex%20has%20always%20been%20the%20quickest%20and%20most%20direct%20way%20to%20earn%20money%20in%20times%20of%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Laura%20Mar%C3%ADa%20Agust%C3%ADn%2C%20an%20anthropologist%20who%20studies%20informal%20labor%20markets%20and%20sex%20work.%20That%20was%20especially%20true%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20which%20made%20sex%20work%20more%20visible%20%E2%80%94%20and%20arguably%20more%20mainstream%20%E2%80%94%20than%20ever%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20watching%20the%20BBC%20documentary%20%26quot%3BStrippers%26quot%3B%20and%20seeing%20how%20much%20its%20subjects%20earned%2C%20Alex%20began%20stripping%20to%20support%20herself%20while%20in%20school.%20Having%20grown%20up%20partly%20in%20the%20foster%20care%20system%2C%20the%2028-year-old%20learned%20to%20be%20independent%20early%20on.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20quite%20entrepreneurial%20and%20come%20from%20a%20background%20where%20I%20didn't%20have%20money%2C%20so%20I%20was%20chasing%20after%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20After%20graduating%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Edinburgh%20in%202019%2C%20she%20continued%20stripping%20until%20landing%20a%20job%20as%20an%20executive%20recruiter%20in%20August%202020.%20Her%20starting%20salary%20for%20the%20office%20job%20was%20%C2%A320%2C000%2C%20about%20%2427%2C000%2C%20which%20dropped%20to%20%C2%A318%2C000%20after%20three%20months%2C%20with%20commission%20expected%20to%20make%20up%20the%20difference.%20Over%20half%20of%20her%20take-home%20pay%20went%20toward%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20pandemic%2C%20she%20experimented%20with%20camming%E2%80%94%20live-streaming%20adult%20content%20for%20paying%20viewers%20%E2%80%94%20for%20extra%20cash.%20She%20also%20tried%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-money-on-onlyfans-according-to-creators-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOnlyFans%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20she%20quickly%20realized%20required%20relentless%20promotion.%20%26quot%3BYou%20do%20not%20know%20the%20slog%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20laughs.%20%26quot%3BNot%20a%20dollar%20was%20made.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20friend%20from%20the%20strip%20club%20started%20escorting%2C%20Alex%20became%20curious%20about%20the%20lifestyle%20and%20the%20money%20she%20could%20make.%20A%20few%20months%20into%20her%20job%20as%20a%20recruiter%2C%20she%20began%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpsychopath-woman-wall-street-escort-success-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eescorting%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20side.%20Soon%20she%20was%20making%20%C2%A36%2C000%20a%20month.%20Within%20two%20years%2C%20she%20left%20her%20day%20job.%20%26quot%3BMy%20managers%20weren't%20respecting%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20this%20idea%20that%20as%20a%20junior%20you're%20supposed%20to%20get%20your%20head%20down%20and%20slog%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20encourage%20independent%2C%20critical%20thinking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222311%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portraits%20of%20%26quot%3BZoe%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682e3d49c6ad288d14819758%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221509%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20sex%20workers%20entered%20the%20industry%20after%20having%20a%20difficult%20time%20finding%20a%20decent%20job%20after%20graduating%20from%20college.%3Cp%3EAyesha%20Kazim%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMaria%2C%2028%2C%20also%20turned%20to%20sex%20work%20after%20growing%20disillusioned%20with%20traditional%20employment.%20She'd%20worked%20as%20a%20paralegal%20in%20Australia%20before%20moving%20to%20London%2C%20where%20she%20took%20a%20job%20as%20a%20receptionist%20at%20a%20law%20firm.%20The%20longer%20hours%2C%20lower%20pay%2C%20and%20lack%20of%20flexibility%20quickly%20wore%20her%20down.%20It%20wasn't%20until%20she%20met%20a%20colleague%20%E2%80%94%20a%20fellow%20receptionist%20who%20supplemented%20her%20income%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpole-dancing-in-ukraine-strip-club-by-russian-border-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edancing%20in%20strip%20clubs%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20that%20she%20began%20to%20consider%20a%20different%20path.%20Soon%2C%20she%20traded%20the%20legal%20office%20for%20strip%20clubs%20across%20London%20and%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELately%2C%20though%2C%20the%20work%20hasn't%20been%20as%20lucrative.%20Maria%20says%20that%20despite%20six%20years%20of%20experience%2C%20she's%20making%20about%20the%20same%20as%20she%20did%20in%202019%20when%20she%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bbaby%20stripper%20and%20didn't%20know%20anything.%26quot%3B%20Back%20then%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere%20was%20way%20more%20foot%20traffic%20in%20the%20clubs.%26quot%3B%20Now%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bcustomers%20are%20definitely%20stingier.%26quot%3B%20She%20earns%20around%20%C2%A35%2C200%20a%20month%20for%20three%20to%20four%20nights%20of%20work%20a%20week.%20%26quot%3BI've%20got%20so%20much%20more%20knowledge%20and%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20I%20should%20be%20making%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaria%20attributes%20that%20to%20the%20economic%20downturn%20of%20the%20past%20few%20years.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20cheaper%20and%20don't%20want%20to%20spend%20as%20much.%20A%20lot%20of%20guys%20are%20still%20saying%2C%20'It's%20the%20cost-of-living%20crisis%2C%20I%20can't%20afford%20that%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20US%20posters%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FSexWorkers%2Fhot%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Er%2Fsexworkers%3C%2Fa%3E%20Reddit%20thread%20said%20they%20began%20noticing%20a%20decline%20in%20earnings%20just%20as%20economists%20started%20talking%20about%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-2025-outlook-what-3-bearish-forecasters-think-will-happen-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erecession%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-liberation-day-reciprocal-tariffs-speech-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20announced%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Recently%2C%20more%20posters%20have%20said%20business%20is%20unusually%20slow%20and%20clients%20are%20more%20demanding.%20Andrew%20Lokenauth%2C%20a%20data%20analyst%20and%20founder%20of%20TheFinanceNewsletter%2C%20who%20has%20tracked%20the%20sex%20work%20industry%20for%2015%20years%2C%20says%20revenue%20at%20clubs%20dropped%20by%2035%25%20to%2040%25%20from%202022%20to%202024%20across%20major%20US%20cities.%20In%20his%20work%20as%20a%20financial%20advisor%20for%20strip%20clubs%2C%20he%20has%20seen%20clubs%20shut%20down%2C%20reduce%20staff%2C%20and%20cut%20back%20their%20hours%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20downturn%2C%20and%20predicts%20more%20will%20close.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStrip%20clubs%20are%20a%20winter%20sport.%20You're%20supposed%20to%20make%20the%20most%20money%20in%20winter%2C%26quot%3B%20Hannah%20says.%20This%20year%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20earnings%20weren't%20as%20good%20as%20we%20thought%20they%20would%20have%20been.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20pandemic%2C%20she%20says%2C%20she%20was%20averaging%20between%20%C2%A35%2C000%20and%20%C2%A37%2C000%20a%20month%20for%20four%20nights%20of%20work%20a%20week.%20Now%2C%20she%20averages%20between%20%C2%A34%2C000%20and%20%C2%A35%2C000%20for%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20work.%20%26quot%3BOlder%20girls%20say%20they%20easily%20made%20%C2%A31%2C000%20a%20night%20before%202008%2C%20but%20now%20that's%20pretty%20rare%20in%20London%2C%26quot%3B%20Hannah%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20adds%20that%20she's%20lucky%20because%20she%20has%20a%20couple%20of%20regulars%20who%20come%20consistently%3B%20she's%20noticed%20a%20lot%20of%20girls%20end%20up%20sitting%20around%20at%20the%20club%20because%20there%20aren't%20enough%20customers.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20still%20make%20good%20money%2C%20but%20you%20just%20have%20to%20work%20really%20hard%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20belt-tightening%20comes%20on%20the%20heels%20of%20years%20of%20upheaval%20in%20the%20industry%20after%20the%20accessibility%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fonlyfans-platform-alternatives-sex-work-entrepreneurs-2020-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esex%20work%20platforms%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fonlyfans-users-annual-earnings-creators-2023-spend-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOnlyFans%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20AdultWork%20flooded%20the%20market%20with%20sex%20workers.%20Camille%20Sojit%20Pejcha%2C%20a%20journalist%20and%20the%20author%20of%20the%20sex%20and%20culture%20newsletter%20Pleasure-Seeking%2C%20says%20this%20%26quot%3Bcreated%20a%20new%20hierarchy%20that%20rewards%20celebrities%20and%20influencers%20while%20pushing%20everyday%20sex%20workers%20to%20the%20margins.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20are%20still%20OnlyFans%20creators%20pulling%20in%20over%20%24100%2C000%20a%20month%2C%20Lokenauth%20says%20average%20monthly%20earnings%20on%20the%20platform%20dropped%20from%20about%20%24600%20to%20under%20%24200%20in%20two%20years.%20%26quot%3BI've%20interviewed%20sex%20workers%20and%20ghostwriters%20at%20major%20agencies%2C%20and%20they%20all%20say%20the%20same%20thing%3A%20'There%20is%20no%20middle%20class%20in%20sex%20work%20anymore%2C'%26quot%3B%20Pejcha%20says.%20(Many%20top%20creators%20on%20OnlyFans%20now%20hire%20ghostwriters%20to%20write%20posts%20and%20reply%20to%20messages.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECharlotte%20saw%20this%20firsthand.%20She%20began%20stripping%20at%2019%20while%20in%20college%2C%20just%20before%20the%202008%20recession%20slashed%20corporate%20entertainment%20budgets%20and%20sent%20club%20earnings%20into%20decline.%20She%20left%20the%20industry%20in%20her%20early%2020s%20and%20moved%20into%20conventional%20work.%20Now%20in%20her%20mid-30s%20and%20paying%20off%20a%20mortgage%20after%20buying%20a%20flat%20in%20London%2C%20she%20returned%20to%20sex%20work%20last%20year%20%E2%80%94%20this%20time%20as%20an%20escort.%20After%20a%20decade%20away%2C%20she%20found%20herself%20in%20a%20very%20different%20landscape%20%E2%80%94%20one%20where%20oversaturation%2C%20falling%20rates%2C%20and%20burnout%20have%20become%20the%20norm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-warned-great-recession-2008-brooksley-born-wall-street-sexism-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E2008%20financial%20crash%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20said%2C%20she%20was%20making%20up%20to%20%C2%A32%2C000%20a%20night%20dancing%20in%20a%20strip%20club.%20She%20expected%20escorting%20to%20yield%20even%20more%2C%20given%20the%20greater%20level%20of%20intimacy%20involved.%20But%20her%20rates%20have%20capped%20out%20at%20%C2%A3300%20to%20%C2%A3400%20an%20hour%2C%20and%20she%20averages%20%C2%A31%2C000%20to%20%C2%A33%2C000%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20often%20less%20than%20what%20she%20once%20earned%20in%20a%20single%20night%20during%20the%20strip-club%20boom%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20finding%20it%20hard%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThis%20just%20doesn't%20feel%20normal%20%E2%80%94%20am%20I%20the%20only%20one%20struggling%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECharlotte%20attributes%20the%20shift%20to%20the%20glutted%20market.%20%26quot%3BIt%20ruined%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BMen%20could%20buy%20sex%20as%20cheaply%20as%20ordering%20Uber%20Eats.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20so%20much%20competition%20for%20bookings%2C%20even%20self-described%20%26quot%3Bhigh-end%26quot%3B%20escorts%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bposh%20English%20girls%20with%20premium%20high%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Charlotte%20puts%20it%20%E2%80%94%20were%20forced%20to%20adapt.%20%26quot%3BEven%20those%20of%20us%20on%20AdultWork%20dropped%20our%20rates%20to%20ensure%20we%20got%20bookings%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%C2%A31%2C000%20to%20%C2%A33%2C000%20a%20week%20may%20seem%20like%20good%20money%20to%20many%2C%20Charlotte%20argues%20that%20the%20nature%20of%20sex%20work%20%E2%80%94%20which%20she%20describes%20as%20intrinsically%20%26quot%3Bviolent%26quot%3B%20and%20often%20dangerous%20%E2%80%94%20warrants%20a%20higher%20rate%20of%20return.%20%26quot%3BSex%20work%20should%20be%20high%20reward%20and%20high%20payoff%20money-wise%2C%20because%20a%20lot%20of%20us%20suffer%20in%20doing%20this%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20about%20survival%2C%20getting%20enough%20money%20to%20survive.%20I%20would%20never%20in%20a%20million%20years%20want%20to%20sleep%20with%20any%20of%20these%20men.%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20paid%20insanely%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20women%20I%20spoke%20with%20initially%20saw%20sex%20work%20as%20a%20loophole%20in%20the%20labor%20market%20where%2C%20if%20you%20hustled%20hard%20enough%2C%20you%20could%20achieve%20financial%20autonomy%20faster%20than%20traditional%20jobs%20allow.%20For%20a%20generation%20raised%20on%20self-branding%20and%20self-reliance%2C%20it%20promised%20flexibility%2C%20autonomy%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20%E2%80%94%20a%20kind%20of%20shortcut%20to%20the%20American%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20slowdown%20shows%20that%20sex%20work%20is%20governed%20by%20the%20same%20market%20forces%20as%20any%20other%20sector.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstanfordeconreview.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F01%2Fcook-et-al-prostitution.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%20examined%20prostitution%20after%20the%202008%20recession%20and%20found%20that%20it%20%26quot%3B%20is%20more%20sensitive%20to%20changes%20in%20unemployment%2C%20income%2C%20or%20other%20macro%20factors%20that%20decrease%20consumer%20demand.%26quot%3B%20In%20other%20words%2C%20when%20the%20economy%20contracts%2C%20so%20does%20the%20sex%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20the%20easy%20money%20from%20the%20boom%20days%20has%20changed%20their%20view%20of%20pursuing%20other%20kinds%20of%20work.%20Asia%20de%20la%20Rosa%20was%2015%20when%20the%20pandemic%20began%20and%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-sell-feet-pics-online-find-clients-prices-anonymous-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eselling%20foot%20pics%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20catfishing%20content%20on%20Snapchat.%20She%20began%20making%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20money%20I've%20ever%20touched%20in%20my%20life%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20%2445%2C000%20in%20one%20summer.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20app%20cracked%20down%20on%20sex%20work%20and%20banned%20her%20profile%2C%20but%20the%20money%20changed%20her%20view%20on%20life.%20Now%2020%20and%20working%20in%20a%20bodega%20in%20Manhattan%20for%20%2416%20an%20hour%2C%20she%20is%20uninterested%20in%20pursuing%20a%20conventional%20career.%20%26quot%3BSeeing%20how%20much%20money%20I%20made%2C%20going%20back%20to%20regular%20work%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20like%2C%20'That's%20not%20my%20worth%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20She%20still%20occasionally%20sells%20foot%20pictures%20to%20fetishists%20on%20the%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222311%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portraits%20of%20Asia%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682e3d71ac40ae2b0c9eb734%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221509%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAsia%20de%20la%20Rosa%20made%20so%20much%20money%20doing%20sex%20work%20that%20she%20is%20no%20longer%20interested%20in%20conventional%20work.%3Cp%3ELanna%20Apisukh%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlex%20is%20also%20uninterested%20in%20going%20back%20on%20the%20job%20market%3B%20she's%20having%20a%20good%20time%20and%20earning%20up%20to%20%C2%A310%2C000%20a%20month.%20She's%20able%20to%20weather%20the%20effects%20of%20saturation%2C%20because%20%26quot%3Bclients%20who%20like%20me%2C%20still%20like%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20She%20plans%20to%20keep%20escorting%20until%20she's%2035%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20longer.%20%26quot%3BI%20give%20people%20a%20lot%20of%20joy%2C%20and%20I'd%20feel%20bad%20for%20them%20if%20I%20was%20to%20stop.%26quot%3B%20If%20she%20pivots%20in%20the%20future%2C%20she%20could%20imagine%20starting%20her%20own%20business%20or%20working%20for%20herself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20who%20aren't%20starting%20their%20own%20ventures%2C%20the%20tough%20job%20market%20is%20making%20it%20increasingly%20difficult%20to%20transition%20out%20of%20sex%20work.%20Zoe%2C%20who's%2032%20and%20has%20been%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20industry%20for%20a%20decade%2C%20worries%20that%20her%20decision%20to%20go%20into%20sex%20work%20may%20cost%20her%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20%26quot%3BHow%20am%20I%20going%20to%20explain%20two%20years%20out%20of%20work%20on%20my%20CV%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20asks.%20She%20puts%20%26quot%3Bclient%20relations%26quot%3B%20on%20her%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20but%20when%20recruiters%20ask%20for%20examples%2C%20she's%20stumped.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20say%2C%20'I%20do%20dinner%20dates%20with%20executives%20from%20Google.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaria%20also%20worries%20about%20her%20ability%20to%20transition%20into%20more%20conventional%20work%20in%20her%2030s.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20got%20into%20the%20industry%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20any%20career%20goals.%20I've%20always%20been%20a%20'live%20in%20the%20moment'%20kind%20of%20person%20%E2%80%94%20do%20what%20makes%20you%20happy%20right%20now%20%E2%80%94%20and%20stripping%20fit%20that%20mentality.%20But%20after%20living%20in%20the%20present%20for%20maybe%20a%20bit%20too%20long%2C%20I've%20realized%20I%20haven't%20really%20figured%20out%20what%20I%20want%20to%20do.%20So%20in%20that%20sense%2C%20stripping%20may%20have%20held%20me%20back.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelissa%20Ditmore%2C%20who%20has%20researched%20the%20sex%20work%20industry%20in%20the%20US%2C%20says%20this%20dynamic%20is%20typical%20these%20days.%20%26quot%3BSome%20of%20this%20is%20relate