e%20does%20bounce%20back%2C%20especially%20with%20targeted%20restoration%2C%20resilient%20species%2C%20and%20community%20monitoring.%20But%20in%20others%2C%20the%20damage%20changes%20the%20local%20ecology%20forever%2C%20altering%20which%20species%20survive%2C%20how%20food%20chains%20function%2C%20and%20how%20safe%20the%20area%20is%20for%20fishing%20and%20recreation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20while%20recovery%20is%20possible%2C%20the%20effects%20of%20an%20oil%20spill%20don%E2%80%99t%20simply%20vanish%20with%20time.%20They%20fade%20%E2%80%94%20slowly%2C%20unevenly%2C%20and%20sometimes%2C%20never%20completely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMini%20Glossary%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Col%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EFurnace%20Oil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3EA%20heavy%2C%20thick%20fuel%20commonly%20used%20in%20ships%20and%20factories%2C%20it%20is%20slow%20to%20break%20down%20and%20difficult%20to%20clean%20when%20spilled%20in%20water.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3ECalcium%20Carbide%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3EAn%20industrial%20chemical%20that%20reacts%20dangerously%20with%20water%20to%20release%20acetylene%20gas%2C%20which%20is%20flammable%20and%20potentially%20toxic.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EPlankton%20Blooms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3EA%20rapid%20increase%20in%20microscopic%20marine%20organisms%20that%20form%20the%20base%20of%20the%20food%20chain%20and%20help%20support%20fish%20breeding.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EMolluscs%20and%20Crustaceans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3EMarine%20animals%20like%20clams%2C%20snails%2C%20crabs%2C%20and%20prawns%20are%20essential%20to%20coastal%20ecosystems%20and%20local%20fisheries.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3ECoral%20Polyps%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3ETiny%20marine%20animals%20that%20build%20coral%20reefs%20are%20sensitive%20to%20pollution%20and%20critical%20to%20underwater%20biodiversity