0be%20damaging.%20It%20can%20isolate%20people%2C%20prevent%20them%20from%20seeking%20help%2C%20and%20deepen%20the%20fear%20around%20something%20that%E2%80%99s%20already%20misunderstood.%20Understanding%20the%20difference%20is%20the%20first%20step%20to%20treating%20people%20with%20empathy%2C%20not%20fear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMyth%202%3A%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20with%20schizophrenia%20are%20always%20dangerous%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMovies%20often%20show%20people%20with%20schizophrenia%20as%20violent%20or%20unpredictable%20%E2%80%94%20someone%20lashing%20out%2C%20losing%20control%2C%20or%20whispering%20to%20themselves%20before%20doing%20something%20terrifying.%20But%20real%20life%20is%20very%20different.%20In%20reality%2C%20schizophrenia%20often%20looks%20quieter%2C%20more%20inward%2C%20and%20far%20more%20complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImagine%20someone%20who%20spends%20their%20afternoons%20sketching%2C%20listening%20to%20music%2C%20and%20helping%20around%20the%20house.%20They%E2%80%99re%20gentle%2C%20kind%2C%20and%20perhaps%20a%20little%20withdrawn.%20On%20some%20days%2C%20they%20might%20seem%20distant%20or%20distracted%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20they%E2%80%99re%20hearing%20a%20voice%20no%20one%20else%20can%20hear%20or%20feel%20convinced%20that%20people%20are%20watching%20them%2C%20whispering%20things%20that%20aren%E2%80%99t%20really%20being%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%229669016977%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20you%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20isn%E2%80%99t%20danger.%20You%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20someone%20trying%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20a%20world%20that%20suddenly%20feels%20unfamiliar%20or%20overwhelming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHallucinations%20are%20when%20someone%20hears%2C%20sees%2C%20or%20feels%20something%20that%20isn%E2%80%99t%20really%20there.%20Delusions%20are%20fixed%20false%20beliefs%2C%20like%20thinking%20people%20are%20trying%20to%20harm%20you%2C%20or%20that%20you%20have%20extraordinary%20powers%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr.%20Khanna%20explained.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20symptoms%20are%20different%20for%20each%20person%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20make%20someone%20dangerous.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F136309%2Fmental-health-stigma-taboos-depression%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindividuals%20with%20schizophrenia%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20vulnerable%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20harm%20than%20to%20cause%20it.%20Many%20live%20with%20fear%2C%20confusion%2C%20or%20distress%2C%20not%20aggression.%20The%20assumption%20that%20someone%20with%20schizophrenia%20is%20unsafe%20often%20leads%20to%20isolation%20and%20shame%2C%20making%20recovery%20even%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMyth%203%3A%20%E2%80%9CThey%20can%E2%80%99t%20live%20normal%20lives%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20diagnosis%20of%20schizophrenia%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20life%20stops.%20With%20access%20to%20the%20right%20care%2C%20many%20people%20continue%20to%20work%2C%20build%20relationships%2C%20raise%20families%2C%20and%20live%20independently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20entirely%20possible%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dr.%20Khanna.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20key%20is%20consistent%20treatment%2C%20which%20includes%20regular%20medication%2C%20therapy%2C%20and%20strong%20support%20from%20family%20or%20caregivers.%E2%80%9D%20She%20emphasises%20that%20schizophrenia%20requires%20ongoing%20care%2C%20and%20stopping%20treatment%20abruptly%20can%20lead%20to%20relapses.%20But%20stability%20and%20fulfilment%20are%20very%20much%20within%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20people%20return%20to%20jobs%2C%20reconnect%20with%20loved%20ones%2C%20and%20m